The problem is that we have added extra elements and attributes outside of the namespace declaration. Let's try to clean up the XML.

```xml}
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<ns:Mission xmlns:ns="http://example.com/mission.xsd"
             xsi:schemaLocation="http://example.com/mission.xsd http://example.com/mission.xsd#"
             xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
  <CompositeTaskInformation>
    <!-- composite task information -->
    <TaskDescription xml:lang="en-US">Drive to the northern most tree and take a picture</TaskDescription>
    <DrivingAction>
      <StartLocation ref="#tree_18"/>
      <EndLocation ref="#eastern_middle_point"/>
      <Distance unit="kilometers">0.01</Distance>
    </DrivingAction>
    <TaskDescription xml:lang="en-US">Take another task</TaskDescription>
  </CompositeTaskInformation>

  <!-- composite task information -->
  <CompositeTaskInformation id="2">
    <TaskDescription xml:lang="en-US">Another driving action</TaskDescription>
    <DrivingAction>
      <StartLocation ref="#tree_20"/>
      <EndLocation ref="#eastern_middle_point_2"/>
      <Distance unit="kilometers">0.02</Distance>
    </DrivingAction>
  </CompositeTaskInformation>

  <!-- tree locations -->
  <Tree id="3" x="4" y="5"/>
</ns:Mission>
```

In this updated version, we've removed the extra elements and attributes outside of the namespace declaration. We can now use the `xsi:schemaLocation` attribute to specify the schema location for our XML document.